This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a new optimization algorithm for stochastic optimization. It also involves computational graph and automatic differentiation, which are commonly used in machine learning. 

It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as optimization is a fundamental problem in AI and the proposed algorithm could potentially improve the performance of AI models. 

The paper also mentions experimental results on multiple datasets and network models, which suggests it could belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as these fields often involve training complex models on large datasets. 

Finally, the paper analyzes the theoretical convergence properties and implementation of the algorithm, which could make it relevant to cs.SY (Systems and Control) as well.
